## 3. Build instructions

Assuming the files are placed as follows:

```
src/
 ├─ pcapng.mli
 ├─ pcapng.ml          (empty – the implementation lives in the C stub)
 └─ pcapng_stubs.c
```

Create a tiny `pacakage.ml` that just includes the compiled stub:

```ocaml
(* pcapng.ml – nothing but the external declarations *)
external open_file : string -> Pcapng.t = "caml_pcapng_open_file"
external close    : Pcapng.t -> unit = "caml_pcapng_close"
external iter     : Pcapng.t -> (Pcapng.frame -> unit) -> unit = "caml_pcapng_iter"
external next_opt : Pcapng.t -> Pcapng.frame option = "caml_pcapng_next_opt"

(* Register the End_of_file exception at library load time *)
let () = ignore (Caml.Prim.caml_pcapng_register_exn ())
```

Now compile:

```sh
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Build the C++ stub (needs a C++ compiler)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
ocamlc -c -I +camlp4 pcapng.mli
g++ -I$(ocamlc -where) -I. -fPIC -c pcapng_stubs.c -o pcapng_stubs.o

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Build the OCaml part
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
ocamlc -c pcapng.ml

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Archive the native library
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
ocamlmklib -o pcapng pcapng_stubs.o -lpcapng   # <-- link with the real libpcapng

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Use the library from an OCaml program
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
ocamlc -I . -o test \
       pcapng.cma test.ml
```

(If you are using **Dune**, the rule for the stub looks like:

```dune
(library
 (name pcapng)
 (foreign_stubs
  (language c)
  (flags (:standard -I${ocaml_where}))
  (names pcapng_stubs))
 (cxx_flags -std=c++11)
 (libraries pcapng)          ; link with the real libpcapng
 (modules pcapng))
```

Dune will invoke `g++` automatically for the `cxx` flag.)

